The Electron Shells · node ATM · ATM · The electrons' quantized energy levels — shells K, L, M, N (n = 1, 2, 3, 4…), each holding up to 2n² electrons (2, 8, 18, 32), filled bottom-up under the Pauli exclusion principle. Held by the ELECTROMAGNETIC force.

universe of origin : ATM · The Atom
seal               : IS THE PERIODIC TABLE. The outermost (valence) shell decides every chemical property — why sodium is reactive and neon is inert. Transitions between shells cost a few eV → visible light. This is the CHEMISTRY shell system.
